1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning to estimate human pose in still images using a probabilistic framework and deep probabilistic networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to reduce the cost of training by using a diverse data set and employs two distributions to estimate the parameters. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with learning to estimate human pose using a probabilistic framework and deep learning techniques. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with estimating human pose in still images, which is a common task in multimedia analysis. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with estimating human pose, which is relevant to robotics applications such as human-robot interaction and manipulation.
